18/08/2006
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The government approved an action plan Thursday (17 August) to enhance its capacity to absorb European structural and cohesion funds which Romania can access after becoming a member of the Union. Cristian David, minister-delegate for the control of internationally financed programmes and the implementation of the EU acquis, explained that the utilisation of EU funds is a priority. He added that Romania would be entitled to receive about 18 billion euros from 2007-2013, while its contribution to the EU budget would be 7.5 billion euros. (Rompres - 17/08/06)
